+var employeeLabel = [], employeeSalaryData = [], employeeDateData = []
+
+async function dummyChart() {
+  await getDummyData()
+
+const ctx = document.getElementById('myChart').getContext('2d');
+
+const chart = new Chart(ctx, {
+    // The type of chart we want to create
+    type: 'line',
+
+    // The data for our dataset
+    data: {
+        labels: employeeLabel,
+        datasets: [{
+            label: 'Employee Salary',
+            backgroundColor: '',
+            borderColor: '#0A2558',
+            data: employeeSalaryData
+        },
+        {
+          label: 'Employee Date',
+          backgroundColor: '',
+          borderColor: '#0A2558',
+          data: employeeDateData
+      }
+      ]
+    },
+
+    // Configuration options go here
+    options: {
+      tooltips: {
+        mode: 'index'
+      }
+    }
+})}
+
+dummyChart()
+
+
+//Fetch Data from API
+
+async function getDummyData() {
+  const apiUrl = "https://andrealeporialeide.github.io/invest.io/public/dummy-chart-main/restapi.json";
+
+  const response = await fetch(apiUrl)
+  const barChatData = await response.json()
+  
+  const salary = barChatData.data.map((x) => x.employee_salary)
+  console.log(salary)
+  const Date = barChatData.data.map((x) => x.employee_Date)
+  const date = barChatData.data.map((x) => x.employee_date)
+
+ employeeSalaryData = salary
+ employeeDateData = Date
+ employeeLabel = date
+}
